msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:51
msgid "Typography & design tokens"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:52
msgid "One consistent typeface and tidier labels across the builder."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:53
msgid "Applies one consistent typeface across the builder and tidies field labels, group headings and panel shadows to match."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:59
msgid "Tab styling"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:60
msgid "Clear accent underlines on every tab in the builder."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:61
msgid "Gives every tab in the builder a clear underline in the accent colour (panel tabs, document tabs, scope switchers and settings tabs), and widens the search field in the CSS vars tab."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:67
msgid "Search field icons"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:68
msgid "Adds the missing magnifying-glass icons to search fields."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:69
msgid "Adds a magnifying-glass icon to the builder search fields that lack one (the Navigator filter and the CSS vars search) so each reads as a search box at a glance. The Inserter search keeps its own built-in icon."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:75
msgid "Controls styling"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:76
msgid "Restyles buttons, inputs and dropdowns with accessible contrast."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:77
msgid "Restyles buttons, inputs, dropdowns, segmented radios and the element inserter with the plugin's colour palette, meeting WCAG AA contrast."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:83
msgid "Focus visibility"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:84
msgid "A visible focus ring on every control."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:85
msgid "Shows a visible focus ring on every interactive control in the builder, as required by WCAG 2.4.7."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:91
msgid "Navigator row styling"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:92
msgid "Larger, easier-to-scan Navigator rows."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:93
msgid "Makes Navigator rows larger and easier to scan, with clear hover and selected states. The decorative drag-handle strip is removed; dragging still works."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:99
msgid "Theme switcher (light / dark / auto)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:100
msgid "Light, dark or follow-the-OS builder theme."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:101
msgid "Adds a top-bar button that switches the builder between light and dark themes, or follows your operating system automatically."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:107
msgid "Density toggle"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:108
msgid "Comfortable or compact spacing, switched from the top bar."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:109
msgid "Adds a top-bar button that switches panel and Navigator spacing between comfortable and compact."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:115
msgid "Top-bar keyboard groups"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:116
msgid "Screen-reader grouping and arrow keys for the top-bar controls."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:117
msgid "Gives the top-bar control clusters proper grouping for screen readers and keyboard users: the breakpoint switcher becomes a radio group (announces which breakpoint is current, arrow keys move and select it, one Tab stop), and the canvas width and zoom fields are grouped and labelled."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:123
msgid "Bottom-bar keyboard toolbar"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:124
msgid "Makes the bottom tool bar one Tab stop with arrow keys."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:125
msgid "Wires the bottom bar of editor tools (Custom CSS, JavaScript, Dynamic Data, Sense AI and so on) as a keyboard toolbar: one Tab stop with arrow-key navigation, each tool announces whether its panel is open, the shared panel is a labelled region, and locked tools are announced as such. Also wires the Global / Template scope tabs inside the JavaScript and Dynamic Data tools as a vertical tab list."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:131
msgid "Accessible select comboboxes"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:132
msgid "Keyboard and screen-reader support for the custom selects."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:133
msgid "Makes the builder's custom select popovers (the preview picker, the responsive-strategy select, the element HTML-tag select and others) usable with a screen reader and the keyboard: proper combobox / listbox / option roles, one Tab stop, and arrow keys to move through the options with Enter to choose. Purely additive — typing to filter and clicking to choose are left to Builderius."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:139
msgid "Accessible AI session tabs"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:140
msgid "Proper tabs and keyboard access for the Sense AI sessions."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:141
msgid "Wires the Sense AI terminal session tabs (Claude Code, Gemini CLI and so on) as a proper tab list for screen readers and the keyboard: the tabs announce which session is active, arrow keys move between them and switch with one Tab stop, the terminal below is exposed as their tab panel, and the \"new session\" button gets a clear name in place of its bare plus sign, plus a proper pop-up menu (arrow keys to choose an agent, Escape to close). Purely additive: clicking to switch is left to Builderius."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:147
msgid "Accessible panel tabs"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:148
msgid "Arrow-key tab strips in the settings panel and Navigator."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:149
msgid "Wires the panel tab strips as proper tab lists for screen readers and the keyboard: the settings panel's Content / Styles tabs and the Navigator's Elements / Selectors / CSS vars tabs. Each tab announces that it is a tab and whether it is current, and each strip becomes one Tab stop where the arrow keys move between the tabs and switch them (Home and End jump to the first and last)."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:157
msgid "HTML tag badges"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:158
msgid "Shows each element's HTML tag in the Navigator."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:159
msgid "Shows each element's HTML tag (such as <section>) next to its label in the Navigator, in place of its first CSS class."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:165
msgid "Tidier Navigator icons"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:166
msgid "Hides repeated Navigator icons, keeping the meaningful ones."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:167
msgid "Hides the repeated element-type icons in the Navigator, keeping only the ones that carry meaning (Collections and Templates)."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:173
msgid "Collapse & expand buttons"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:174
msgid "One-click expand or collapse of the whole tree."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:175
msgid "Adds two buttons to the Navigator header: one expands every row, the other collapses the tree down to its top-level sections."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:182
msgid "Navigator search"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:183
msgid "A filter box for the Navigator tree."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:184
msgid "Adds a filter box above the tree that dims any row whose label or HTML tag does not match what you type."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:191
#: includes/i18n-builder.php:302
msgid "Rearrange favourites"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:192
msgid "Drag or arrow-key reordering of the favourites bar."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:193
msgid "Adds a rearrange button to the favourites bar. Drag the icons, or use the arrow keys, to put them in your preferred order; the order is remembered in your browser."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:200
msgid "Follow selection in the tree"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:201
msgid "The tree opens and scrolls to whatever you select."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:202
msgid "When you click an element in the preview, the Navigator opens the branches down to it and scrolls it into view, so your selection is never hidden in a collapsed part of the tree."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:208
msgid "Navigator keyboard tree"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:209
msgid "Full arrow-key navigation of the tree, WordPress style."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:210
msgid "Makes the Navigator behave like the WordPress list view: the arrow keys move through the elements (the canvas selection follows), the right arrow opens a branch and steps into it, the left arrow closes it and steps out to the parent, and Home and End jump to the first and last. The tree is exposed to screen readers as a proper tree, so each element announces its level, whether it is expanded, and its position."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:216
msgid "Detachable Navigator"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:217
msgid "Float the Navigator over the canvas."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:218
msgid "Adds a detach button to the Navigator header so you can float the panel over the canvas. Drag it by its header, resize it from the bottom corner, and dock it again with the same button. Its position is remembered. Experimental: it floats the panel over the builder chrome, so a Builderius update could shift it."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:227
msgid "Right-click menu enhancements"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:228
msgid "A flatter, keyboard-friendly right-click menu."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:229
msgid "Reorganises the Navigator right-click menu into one flat, logically grouped list, so everyday actions are one click away. Includes full keyboard support (arrow keys, Home/End, Escape) and keeps submenus only where an action branches (Wrap in…, Save to…). Also adds a right-click copy and remove menu to the class chips in the Styles editor."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:236
msgid "Wrap in… / Unwrap"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:237
msgid "Wrap elements in a div, template or collection - and unwrap."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:238
msgid "Right-click an element to wrap it in a div, a template or a collection with template. Unwrap does the reverse: it moves the children up one level and removes the empty wrapper."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:245
msgid "Move & navigate elements"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:246
msgid "Move up, move down and select parent in the right-click menu."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:247
msgid "Adds Move up, Move down and Select parent to the right-click menu, so you can reorder an element among its siblings or step the selection up a level."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:253
msgid "Inline rename"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:254
msgid "Rename an element directly on its Navigator row."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:255
msgid "Lets you rename an element directly on its Navigator row from the right-click menu, or reset its label to the default (its HTML tag)."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:262
msgid "Double-click to rename"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:263
msgid "Double-click a row to rename it."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:264
msgid "Double-click an element's Navigator row to rename it in place, without opening the right-click menu."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:270
msgid "Undo / redo add & delete"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:271
msgid "Cmd/Ctrl+Z restores deleted elements and undoes adds."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:272
msgid "Press Cmd/Ctrl+Z to undo adding or deleting an element: a deleted element is restored, and one you just added is removed. Add Shift (Cmd/Ctrl+Shift+Z) to redo. A brief message confirms each step. Moving elements and changing their settings are not covered."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:289
msgid "Rearrange component properties"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:290
msgid "Drag or arrow-key reordering of component properties."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:291
msgid "Adds a rearrange button to a component's properties panel. Drag the properties, or use the arrow keys, to change their order; the new order is saved with the component."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:297
msgid "HTML attribute helpers"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:298
msgid "A ready-to-type attribute row plus common-name suggestions."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:299
msgid "Opens a blank, ready-to-type row when an element has no HTML attributes yet (it is removed again if left empty), and suggests common attribute names such as id, role, aria-* and data-*."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:305
msgid "Inserter keyboard navigation"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:306
msgid "Arrow-key navigation of the element Inserter."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:307
msgid "Makes the element Inserter navigable from the keyboard the way the WordPress block inserter is: each category is one Tab stop, the arrow keys move between the elements within a category (Home and End jump to its first and last), and Enter or Space inserts. Without it, reaching a lower category means tabbing through every element above it."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:313
msgid "Accessible Builderius menu"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:314
msgid "Keyboard and screen-reader access for the Builderius menu."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:315
msgid "Makes the Builderius menu (the sidebar of templates, pages, components and admin links) usable from the keyboard and a screen reader. The menu button announces that it opens the menu, focus moves into it when it opens, and it is exposed as a tree: the arrow keys move between the collapsible category headings and their items, the right and left arrows open and close a category, Enter or Space toggles a heading or opens an item, Home and End jump to the ends, and Escape (or the panel’s Close button) closes the menu and returns focus to the button."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:321
msgid "Element keyboard shortcuts"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:322
msgid "Block-editor-style shortcuts for the selected element."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:323
msgid "Adds keyboard shortcuts, in the style of the WordPress block editor, for the element selected in the Navigator: duplicate (Cmd/Ctrl+Shift+D), cut (Cmd/Ctrl+X), add an element before or after it (Cmd/Ctrl+Alt+T / Cmd/Ctrl+Alt+Y, via a quick element picker) and rename (F2). The new actions also appear in the right-click menu. Plus shortcuts to jump between the builder’s regions (the Navigator, settings panel, canvas and Inserter). Experimental: Builderius is adding its own shortcuts, so this may overlap or be retired."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:331
#: includes/i18n-builder.php:365
#: includes/i18n-builder.php:408
msgid "Command palette"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:332
msgid "A searchable command palette on Cmd/Ctrl+Shift+K."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:333
msgid "Press Cmd/Ctrl+Shift+K for a searchable command palette. With an element selected it can add classes, add HTML attributes and add child elements with a minimal Emmet syntax (e.g. section.hero>h1{Title}+p{Lead}), plus run the element actions and jump between the builder’s regions. Experimental."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:343
msgid "CSS code editor by default"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:344
msgid "Opens the Styles tab straight into the CSS code editor."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:345
msgid "Opens the Styles tab straight into the CSS code editor and keeps the Content and Styles tabs visible while you are there. (To widen the panel for more room, use the Resizable side panels feature.) Requires Builderius Pro: the CSS code editor is a Pro feature, so this stays off (and the CSS-mode icon is left in place) when Pro is inactive."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:352
msgid "CSS scope bar"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:353
msgid "Shows and switches where CSS edits are saved."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:354
msgid "Shows where your CSS edits will be saved (local, global or template) and adds an instant Global/Template switch, directly in the Styles code editor. Also keeps the editor honest: it shows only the active scope’s rules for the selected class, so global and template CSS never look merged, and it hides the other scope’s rules (with a one-click switch) instead of letting you fork them by mistake. Adds an “All CSS” button that jumps to the full stylesheet for the active scope (the same view as Selectors → All CSS) and highlights where the current selector’s rules sit within it. Requires Builderius Pro: global and template CSS scopes, and the code editor it sits in, are Pro features."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:362
#: includes/i18n-builder.php:67
msgid "Auto-BEM"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:363
msgid "Suggested BEM class names for an element and its children."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:364
msgid "Right-click an element and choose Auto-BEM to get suggested block and element class names (such as hero, hero__title and hero__image) for it and everything inside it. Edit any suggestion, then apply them all in one go."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:372
msgid "Hide the code minimap"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:373
msgid "Removes the code editor's minimap strip."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:374
msgid "Removes the minimap (the small code-overview strip on the right of the CSS code editor) and reclaims the width Monaco reserves for it, so long lines run to the edge of the panel. It switches the editor option off inside the builder's bundled Monaco; if a Builderius update ever changes that, it falls back to simply hiding the minimap from view."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:381
msgid "Tidy selector hint"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:382
msgid "A compact, dismissable hint under the CSS editor."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:384
#, php-format
msgid "Replaces Builderius’ two-line %local% / %selector% notification under the CSS editor with a compact, dismissable hint, reclaiming the vertical space for the editor. The full explanation moves into a dialog and is reworded so both tokens are described consistently and breakpoints are explained the same way for each (the stock wording differs between them)."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:392
msgid "Tooltips & accessible names"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:393
msgid "Tooltips and names for the unlabelled icon buttons."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:394
msgid "Adds tooltips and accessible names to around 25 icon-only builder buttons that ship without either."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:400
msgid "Keyboard shortcuts overlay"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:401
msgid "Press ? for a list of keyboard shortcuts."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:402
msgid "Press ? in the builder to see a list of keyboard shortcuts, both the native ones and those added by this plugin."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:408
msgid "Unsaved-changes marker"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:409
msgid "An unsaved-changes marker beside the Save button."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:410
msgid "Shows an “Unsaved” marker next to the Save button whenever the template has changes that would be lost on reload."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:416
msgid "Save with Cmd/Ctrl+S"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:417
msgid "Cmd/Ctrl+S saves the template."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:418
msgid "Saves the template with Cmd/Ctrl+S, the shortcut every editor trains into your fingers, instead of opening the browser’s save-page dialog. It works wherever you are in the builder, including the code editors, just like the WordPress block editor."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:424
msgid "Keyboard access for the Save options menu"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:425
msgid "Opt-in keyboard access for the Save options menu."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:426
msgid "Builderius draws the Save button’s dropdown trigger inside the Save button itself, where no keyboard or screen reader can reach it — the Save to Development / Publish to Live menu is mouse-only. This replaces that trigger with a real button beside Save (announced as a menu, arrow keys inside, Escape to close). Experimental and off by default: it restyles a core control, and the proper fix belongs in Builderius (reported upstream) — this is a stopgap for keyboard users until then."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:433
msgid "Second-tab warning"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:434
msgid "An admin-bar edit link plus a second-tab warning."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:435
msgid "Adds an “Edit template” link to the admin bar on the front end, and warns you before the builder opens in a second tab."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:441
msgid "Preview resize handles"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:442
msgid "Drag handles to resize the preview canvas."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:443
msgid "Adds drag handles to both edges of the preview so you can resize it around the centre, which is handy for container-query work. The width readout updates as you drag and the matching breakpoint lights up as you cross it; past your widest breakpoint you can keep dragging to preview any width up to the full canvas. Experimental: above your widest breakpoint the builder has no canvas size of its own, so the handle sizes the canvas itself — a Builderius update could affect that."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:450
msgid "Resizable side panels"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:451
msgid "Drag to set the side panels' width."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:452
msgid "Adds a drag handle to the inner edge of each side panel so you can set their width. The settings panel and the Navigator share one width, so resizing either resizes both. Your chosen width is remembered. Replaces the old one-shot \"widen settings panel\" button."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:458
msgid "Preview overlay contrast fix"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:459
msgid "Readable labels on the canvas hover and selection overlays."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:460
msgid "Fixes the label colours on the preview's hover and selection overlays, so you can tell the two apart and the labels meet WCAG AA contrast."
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:477
msgid "Default theme"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:479
msgid "Auto (follows the operating system)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:480
msgid "Light"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:481
msgid "Dark"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:487
msgid "Default density"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:489
msgid "Comfortable"
msgstr ""

#: includes/features.php:490
msgid "Compact"
msgstr ""

